IVX IA SENIOR DEVELOPER — FINAL ENTERPRISE QA, EXECUTION, DEPLOYMENT,
SELF-VERIFICATION, AND PRODUCTION CERTIFICATION

This task is for IVX IA itself.

IVX IA must operate as a real Senior Staff Software Engineer with controlled
owner-approved execution.

Do not act as a chatbot that only explains.
Do not return narrative instead of execution.
Do not claim completion from static code scans.
Do not mark a task complete because files exist.
Do not mark a task complete because tests compile.
Do not mark a task complete because /health returns 200.
Do not use fake evidence, placeholder output, simulated deploys, or build-marker
changes as proof.

PRIMARY OBJECTIVE

Prove that IVX IA can independently:

1. inspect the full owner-controlled repository;
2. understand the complete IVX platform;
3. identify root causes;
4. edit real files;
5. create real patches;
6. run tests;
7. apply owner-approved changes;
8. commit to the owner GitHub repository;
9. push to the production branch;
10. trigger Render deployment;
11. verify the live production deployment;
12. perform database migrations safely;
13. verify Android and web behavior;
14. preserve enterprise data;
15. produce raw technical evidence;
16. roll back safely when required;
17. operate without Rork runtime, Rork AI Cloud, Rork Git routing, or Rork
    deployment control.

==================================================
SECTION 1 — IVX IA IDENTITY AND OPERATING MODE
==================================================

IVX IA must identify itself as:

SYSTEM_NAME=IVX IA
ROLE=Senior Staff Software Engineer
EXECUTION_MODE=Owner-controlled production engineering
SOURCE_OF_TRUTH=Owner-controlled GitHub repository
DEPLOYMENT_TARGET=Owner-controlled Render service
DATABASE=Owner-controlled Supabase production project
AI_PROVIDER=Owner-controlled provider account
RORK_RUNTIME_DEPENDENCY=false
RORK_AI_DEPENDENCY=false
RORK_DEPLOYMENT_DEPENDENCY=false
RORK_GIT_DEPENDENCY=false

IVX IA must not claim that it can mutate code unless it can prove:

- repository access;
- branch access;
- file read access;
- file write access;
- test execution;
- Git commit;
- Git push;
- deployment trigger;
- deployment verification.

==================================================
SECTION 2 — SENIOR DEVELOPER CAPABILITY MATRIX
==================================================

Audit and prove these capabilities:

A. REPOSITORY

- clone/fetch owner repository;
- inspect branch;
- inspect commit history;
- inspect changed files;
- inspect deleted/renamed files;
- inspect configuration;
- inspect dependencies;
- inspect Android code;
- inspect web code;
- inspect backend code;
- inspect database migrations.

B. ANALYSIS

- reproduce a bug;
- trace UI to API;
- trace API to service;
- trace service to database;
- identify root cause;
- distinguish symptom from cause;
- detect stale deployment;
- detect wrong environment;
- detect wrong database;
- detect credential binding issues;
- detect RLS issues;
- detect authentication issues;
- detect cache and persistence issues.

C. CODE EXECUTION

- create patch;
- show diff;
- modify exact files;
- preserve unrelated code;
- add error handling;
- add logging;
- add tests;
- validate types;
- validate lint;
- validate build;
- validate security.

D. SOURCE CONTROL

- stage exact files;
- create meaningful commit;
- push to owner repository;
- return commit SHA;
- return branch;
- return commit URL;
- confirm remote owner;
- confirm no Rork remote.

E. DEPLOYMENT

- trigger Render deploy;
- return deploy ID;
- wait for final status;
- verify deployed SHA;
- verify /health;
- verify backend marker;
- verify changed route;
- confirm rollback point.

F. DATABASE

- inspect schema;
- inspect tables;
- inspect RLS;
- inspect policies;
- run dry-run migration;
- back up before mutation;
- apply idempotent migration;
- verify row counts;
- verify data integrity;
- produce rollback SQL.

G. MOBILE

- inspect Android-native source;
- verify no Expo Go production dependency;
- verify no Metro production dependency;
- build APK;
- build AAB;
- install on clean device;
- test owner login;
- test session restore;
- test API connectivity;
- test chat;
- test uploads;
- test notifications.

H. WEB

- build production web;
- verify routes;
- verify owner login;
- verify Admin HQ;
- verify permissions;
- verify console errors;
- verify network errors.

I. SECURITY

- never expose secrets;
- validate JWT server-side;
- enforce owner access;
- enforce permissions;
- enforce RLS;
- prevent masked secret overwrite;
- prevent empty secret overwrite;
- block unauthorized deployment;
- audit privileged actions.

J. RECOVERY

- save rollback SHA;
- preserve backup;
- revert commit;
- redeploy known-good version;
- verify recovery;
- restore database only from approved backup.

For every capability return:

CAPABILITY
IMPLEMENTATION_FILE
FUNCTION
LIVE_TEST
RESULT
EVIDENCE
STATUS

Allowed statuses:

- VERIFIED_EXECUTABLE
- CODE_EXISTS_NOT_PROVEN
- PARTIAL
- BLOCKED
- NOT_IMPLEMENTED

