- require MFA;
- copy permissions;
- apply template;
- revoke access.

Verify enforcement at:

- Android navigation;
- web navigation;
- deep links;
- backend APIs;
- Supabase RLS;
- cached data;
- active sessions.

==================================================
SECTION 7 — IVX IA CHAT QA
==================================================

Test both public AI and owner AI.

PUBLIC CHAT

- general conversation works;
- developer/deploy requests are blocked;
- owner-only actions are blocked;
- no secret or internal execution access;
- meaningful response or structured error;
- no empty answers.

OWNER AI

- owner session required;
- real AI provider response;
- no Rork AI Cloud;
- no fallback presented as success;
- permanent user message ID;
- permanent AI message ID;
- permanent conversation ID;
- Supabase persistence;
- correct ordering;
- no duplicates;
- retry without duplication;
- app restart persistence;
- Render restart persistence;
- image support;
- PDF support;
- voice support;
- long response support.

Run 20 sequential real production messages from the Android UI.

==================================================
SECTION 8 — IVX IA SENIOR DEVELOPER REAL EXECUTION TEST
==================================================

Select one real, low-risk production issue.

The test must not be:

- build marker only;
- text-only version update;
- placeholder;
- fake endpoint;
- simulated deploy.

Required execution:

1. receive bug report;
2. inspect repository;
3. reproduce issue;
4. identify root cause;
5. identify exact file/function;
6. create patch;
7. display diff;
8. run focused tests;
9. run regression tests;
10. request owner approval;
11. apply approved patch;
12. commit to owner GitHub;
13. push to main;
14. trigger Render deployment;
15. wait for LIVE;
16. verify /health;
17. verify changed route;
18. verify Android/web behavior;
19. save proof to Supabase;
20. return rollback instruction.

Required evidence:

TASK_ID
ISSUE
ROOT_CAUSE
FILES_CHANGED
DIFF
TEST_COMMANDS
TEST_RESULTS
COMMIT_SHA
COMMIT_URL
RENDER_DEPLOY_ID
DEPLOYED_SHA
HEALTH_STATUS
ROUTE_TEST
PROOF_LEDGER_ID
ROLLBACK_SHA
FINAL_STATUS

==================================================
SECTION 9 — VARIABLES AND CREDENTIAL PERSISTENCE
==================================================

The encrypted IVX vault is the permanent source of truth.

For every variable verify:

- saved;
- encrypted;
- masked;
- decryptable;
- runtime loaded;
- correctly aliased;
- service bound;
- externally validated;
- survives restart;
- survives redeploy;
- survives container recreation;
- cannot be overwritten by blank value;
- cannot be overwritten by masked placeholder;
- cannot be replaced by invalid credential.

Do not ask the owner for an existing variable unless external validation proves:

- 401;
- 403;
- expired;
- revoked;
- deleted;
- malformed;
- missing everywhere.

